(9, 9, 'How to pour the perfect glass of wine?', '', '<p>Knowing how to pour the perfect glass is not just polite but ensures that you and whoever you are entertaining gets the most enjoyment out of the wine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<img alt="" src="./pic/cv/uploads/20130703/image/1372832968.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1. OPENING THE WINE<br />\r\nThere are many ways to open a bottle of wine with a cork. Whether using a fancy air-pressure gadget or the good old waiter screw opener, they are all good methods and what really matters is drinking the wine after the bottle has been opened. One important thing to remember is, when pulling the cork out, be sure not to pull it very fast, causing the &quot;pop&quot; sound. Although an exciting effect, this is actually not polite.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. POURING THE WINE<br />\r\nLike I said, the important part is the actual drinking of the wine, and to enjoy it. When it comes to pouring the wine, make sure the motion is gentle, and that the neck of the bottle isn&rsquo;t resting or touching the rim of the glass. One additional thing you can do that your guests will appreciate is to have the label of the bottle facing your guest so they can see what you are pouring. This is just a&nbsp; nice way to present your wine, but if you are drinking alone then I wouldn&rsquo;t worry too much about this!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. WHERE TO STOP WHEN YOU POUR<br />\r\nBy the guts! I call the widest part of the glass its belly and when you are pouring make sure the wine level reaches that area and then stop. This allows the wine to have the most contact area with the air in the glass. It will start releasing an aroma and reach its proper potential for drinking.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nKnowing these simple steps isn&rsquo;t about being pretentious; it&rsquo;s to show that you care about getting the most out of a bottle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'en_us'),
