(12, 10, 'Casual entertainment: How to light an informal dinner party.', '', '<p>Add some extra ambience with these clever lighting tips. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At last, the luscious green leaves are back, the sky is turning out of the grey and into the blue, and you jump out of bed with a newfound energy and zest for life.&nbsp; Spring is finally here; there are fresh vegetables at the market, and vibrant colours in abundance. When out and about, you don&rsquo;t even have to remember where you left your scarf and gloves. But the best part about this time of year is being outdoors and one thing I treasure most is having a small gathering with my friends and family, &ldquo;al fresco&rdquo;. A warm breeze, in a courtyard or on a patio, with good food, good wine, and of course, laughter, makes for the perfect occasion, and is a highlight of the season.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd the secret of a casual springtime evening is in the lighting.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOnce you&rsquo;ve gathered your nearest and dearest, figured out the food and wine, pay some extra attention to the lighting at all levels to make a memorable difference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="./pic/cv/uploads/20130703/image/1372833044.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1. LIGHTING AT A LOW LEVEL<br />\r\nThese lights will allow you to mark a pathway for walking and define an area for gathering. Use brown paper sandwich bags and fill as many as you need with sand to weigh them down.&nbsp; Inside the bag, place a tea-light candle. Place them on the ground about 1 meter apart along each side of your pathway or at the edge of the area where you are entertaining.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. AT THE TABLE<br />\r\nBe sure to have plenty of candles on the table. I like them to be laid out randomly, with some in glass jars, in different shapes and sizes. Make them sure they aren&rsquo;t perfumed, you don&rsquo;t want to put your guests off their food!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3. LIGHTS ABOVE THE EYES<br />\r\nAbsolutely no fluorescent lights! Keep it soft and warm. I like to resurrect my Christmas tree lights and mix it with colourful lanterns. This will create a festive mood and provide good general lighting without being too bright.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOnce you&rsquo;ve mastered the lighting, turn the music on, pour your favourite wine and raise a glass. Happy Spring!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'en_us'),
