e of Web browser you are using, the language you prefer, the date and time you are visiting, the site page you have visited and so on. Like many Web sites, we use &quot;cookies,&quot; and we obtain certain types of information when your Web browser accesses Fillmore.com.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span>How we use the information gathered? </span><br />\r\nWe will not sell, transfer or leak any personally identifiable customer information to third-part excluding our site. The information you provided via oral, written and/or media forms, will only be used as described below:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile providing services such as online booking, technical support and marketing, the website and the related service providers will have access to information gathered, which however will be used strictly within the service scope.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur employees at customer service center will review the information you provide while responding to your questions about the product and service at our site.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen you consent to receiving material such as product information, promotional mailings and activities information through e-mail or SMS message from us, the information about you would be shared by us and our affiliated businesses partners. Also, those materials include the promotion and activities information from our site and our business partners. We do have the right to manage and control the information we forward from our business partners, but we are not responsible to assume any consequences arisen from them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe do review the resume and related documents you submit for the hiring process. This information is only used by internal staff.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUnder specific legislative and legal requirements, we will disclose certain information accordingly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn order to safeguard the legitimate rights of our site, also to protect and defend the rights, property and security of others, we will disclose relevant information.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span>Use of Cookies</span><br />\r\nFillmore uses cookies to identify you and the data you have been used, which allow our systems to remember your shopping cart, and other shopping information, as you browse our site. By allowing our systems to set a cookie on your computer, you will not have to log in the password more than once per visit, thereby saving you time while on our site. Moreover, cookies also enable us to learn your interests and enhance your experience on our site. <br />\r\nCookies are alphanumeric identifiers that we transfer to your computer''s hard drive through your Web browser to enable our systems to recognize your browser. You can block or otherwise reject our cookies by instructing your browsers. If you prevent your browser from accepting our cookies, you may still use our site, but certain aspects of the shopping experience with Fillmore may be impacted.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span>Account Information</span><br />\r\nIn order to improve our service quality, please keep all your account information current, including address, payment information, telephone number, e-mail address, and alternate receiver for your order. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span>Privacy Safety</span><br />\r\nWe will exercise commercially reasonable efforts to ensure that your information remains confidential. In order to prevent any lost, abuse, reveal, modification and unauthorized access, we work to protect the security of your information during transmission by using Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) technology, which encrypts information you input. <br />\r\nTo prevent your information being revealed when you make a transaction at our site, all sensitive financial issues (including debit/credit card verified and payment confirmation) are processed by relevant banks directly. Our site does not retain the correlated data.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span>About Links </span><br />\r\nOur site includes third-parties advertising and links to other web sites. However, we do